			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Whats &amp;quot;wrong&amp;quot; with my Bard<a name="29058"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 20 04 11:57 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">1. At Level 17 i bought a new weapon (1H Slashing) and i make up to 35 Dmg with it (at Level 17!). Is there no DMG-Cap at Level 17?</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />

<br />
I THINK there's a cap until lvl 20 if I remember correctly. I was never really up on that, but I remember hearing something to that effect. You also have to remember that your offense and weapon skills aern't that high yet, and it also depends on what the DMG on your weapon is as well as taking into account your attack/weapon skill/offense ratings to how often you hit that high with it.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">2. I use my AE-Spells to Kite in Lake of ill Omen. I thought i can only hit 4 Mobs with my AE-Spells... But it seems to be all i pull... I pull 10 Mobs out of the fort, and they all go down at the same time (not the same time, but near by). At the messages in my Chatwindow says, that more the 4 Mobs get DMG from my AE-Spells... </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
The only AE type song that hits a max of 4 targets is the Desperate Dirge. The rest are all either AE point blank, or have an AE range, and effect anything within it's stated range when sung.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">3. At Level 14 i get the Skill &quot;Wind-Instruments&quot;. The list of this website says, that i have to &quot;train&quot; it (at a Bard-GM) befor i can use it. But i dont have to do that! Same with Dual Wield! I get the skill &quot;automaticly&quot;! </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
You can train in anything, even if you already have it and can use it, to a certain point. I think the only skill you don't innately get is intimidation which can be trained in Freeport. The rest you can &quot;boost&quot; a bit with points if they're too time consuming or hard to manually train in. Mainly, these days the points are just freebies.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
